If you subscribe to my newsletter, you know @moderncitizen comes up often. It is not a maternity brand, but the fact that I’m wearing each of these outfits at 7 months pregnant is a testament to many of the reasons why I have become a devotee of their clothes after discovering them last summer. It’s not easy to find comfortable, well-priced wardrobe workhorses that evolve with you across a wide variety of life stages and occasions, or that appeal just as much to a maximalist in search of interesting basics as a minimalist on the hunt for staples to wear to the office. I’m so thrilled to partner with them on styling their latest collection. #ad

Our son was born on a late August morning after 40 hours of prodromal labor and 20 hours of continuous labor, 10 days past his due date. Needless to say, “worth the wait” took on a whole new meaning. Especially since we also waited a little longer than we expected to take him home. 

I had all the requisite words written out on my birth plan: “delayed cord clamping.” “Uninterrupted golden hour.” “Skin to skin.” The words I heard instead were “meconium aspiration” and “respiratory distress.” He was whisked away immediately while I remained in the bed where I gave birth. My memory is foggy, but I remember weeping as the doctor stitched me up. I wept openly and often in the first two weeks of his life — with worry the first time I visited him in the NICU and saw him hooked up to so many tubes and wires, imagining how uncomfortable it must be. And then with cautious delight the first time a nurse placed him on my bare chest minutes later, searching for his face underneath all the plastic that was helping him breathe.

He’s home now and, the doctors have assured us, completely healthy. Even so, I’ve spent hours just watching his lungs move up and down, up and down, up and down. Someone told me that falling in love with your baby is similar to having a teenage crush: exponential and intoxicating. Each day I fall a little further, and feel a little more defenseless as a result, as if this tiny, weeks-old creature might actually be capable of commandeering my heart. I suppose in many ways he already has. How wrenching and how spectacular, that this is how we are made. ❤️‍🔥

Summer of ‘23 was one for the books, featuring back-to-back sibling weddings and a concerted effort on my part to avoid giving birth on either dance floor. Mission accomplished — although it should be noted that at one point someone dropped a vodka soda near my feet and my mom thought it was amniotic fluid 😌
